doc.after: Venezia is a city of small islands enhanced during the Middle Ages by the dredging of soils to raise the marshy ground above the tides The resulting canals encouraged the flourishing of a nautical culture which proved central to the economy of the city Today those canals still provide the means for transport of goods and people within the city
